THE AMOUNT OF ROOFTOP SOLAR NOW

15:02.268 --> 15:04.303
ACCOUNTS FOR 12% OF THE ELECTRIC

15:04.303 --> 15:05.438
UTILITY'S USERS.

15:05.438 --> 15:06.739
THAT'S MORE THAN 20 TIMES THE

15:06.739 --> 15:08.107
NATIONAL AVERAGE.

15:08.107 --> 15:09.175
IT'S BY FAR THE HIGHEST

15:09.175 --> 15:10.576
PENETRATION OF INDIVIDUAL

15:10.576 --> 15:13.379
ROOFTOP SOLAR IN THE COUNTRY.

15:13.379 --> 15:14.747
BUT IN THIS TROPICAL STATE,

15:14.747 --> 15:16.382
WHERE THE COMBINATION OF SKY-

15:16.382 --> 15:17.750
HIGH ENERGY PRICES, ABUNDANT

15:17.750 --> 15:19.819
SUNSHINE, AND FEDERAL AND STATE

15:19.819 --> 15:22.155
TAX CREDITS MAKES GOING SOLAR A

15:22.155 --> 15:24.190
NO-BRAINER, THE VERY POPULARITY

15:24.190 --> 15:25.658
OF THESE PANELS HAS BECOME A

15:25.658 --> 15:26.492
PROBLEM...

15:26.492 --> 15:27.326
>> SO WE DRIVE UP, AND YOU HAVE

15:27.326 --> 15:28.060
THESE LOVELY SOLAR PANELS ON

15:28.060 --> 15:28.928
YOUR ROOF.

15:28.928 --> 15:30.463
HOW'S THAT WORKING OUT FOR YOU?

15:30.463 --> 15:31.798
>> IT'S NOT.

15:31.798 --> 15:32.665
>> Reporter: NOT WORKING OUT

15:32.665 --> 15:34.233
BECAUSE BY THE TIME AIRCRAFT

15:34.233 --> 15:35.501
MECHANIC CARLTON HO JOINED THE

15:35.501 --> 15:37.170
ROOFTOP SOLAR PARADE IN

15:37.170 --> 15:38.838
SEPTEMBER 2013, THERE WERE SO

15:38.838 --> 15:40.540
MANY PEOPLE IN HIS AREA THAT HAD

15:40.540 --> 15:42.308
INSTALLED PANELS THAT THE LOCAL

15:42.308 --> 15:45.211
UTILITY COMPANY TOLD HIM, "DON'T

15:45.211 --> 15:47.246
TURN ON THAT SWITCH YET."

15:47.246 --> 15:48.014
SO, IT'S JUST A QUESTION OF

15:48.014 --> 15:49.248
TURNING THE SWITCH ON AND YOU

15:49.248 --> 15:50.082
HAVE JUICE.

15:50.082 --> 15:51.150
>> YEAH.

15:51.150 --> 15:52.084
>> Reporter: FROM YOUR OWN ROOF.

15:52.084 --> 15:53.019
>> AND EVERYTHING'S AWESOME!

15:53.019 --> 15:54.387
[LAUGHS]

15:54.387 --> 15:54.854
>> Reporter: BUT IT'S NOT THAT

15:54.854 --> 15:55.688
SIMPLE.

15:55.688 --> 15:57.056
WHEN YOU INSTALL SOLAR PANELS,

15:57.056 --> 15:58.191
YOU'RE STILL RELIANT ON THE

15:58.191 --> 15:59.592
LOCAL UTILITY.

15:59.592 --> 16:00.760
WHEN IT'S DARK OR WHEN THE SUN

16:00.760 --> 16:02.829
ISN'T SHINING, YOU NEED THE GRID

16:02.829 --> 16:04.764
TO PROVIDE ELECTRICITY.

16:04.764 --> 16:06.532
EVEN SO, SOLAR CUSTOMERS HAVE A

16:06.532 --> 16:07.567
FUNDAMENTALLY DIFFERENT

16:07.567 --> 16:10.036
RELATIONSHIP WITH THE UTILITY.

16:10.036 --> 16:11.704
BECAUSE WHEN THE SUNIS SHINING,

16:11.704 --> 16:13.339
ANY EXTRA ENERGY THEIR PANELS

16:13.339 --> 16:15.308
GENERATE IS SUPPLIED BACK TO THE

16:15.308 --> 16:17.310
GRID. THAT EARNS A CREDIT,

16:17.310 --> 16:18.644
FURTHER REDUCING THEIR ELECTRIC

16:18.644 --> 16:20.079
BILL.

16:20.079 --> 16:21.581
IN SOME SECTIONS OF OAHU, WITH

16:21.581 --> 16:23.583
SO MANY HOMEOWNERS GOING SOLAR,

16:23.583 --> 16:25.318
THE UTILITY SAID THE SAFETY AND

16:25.318 --> 16:27.153
RELIABILITY OF THE GRID COULD BE

16:27.153 --> 16:28.588
THREATENED AND IT SLOWED TO A

16:28.588 --> 16:29.956
CRAWL THE APPROVAL OF NEW

16:29.956 --> 16:30.923
SYSTEMS.

16:30.923 --> 16:31.891
>> WE KNOW THERE IS STILL MORE

16:31.891 --> 16:32.625
TO DO.

16:32.625 --> 16:33.559
>> Reporter: COLTON CHING IS

16:33.559 --> 16:34.627
VICE PRESIDENT FOR ENERGY

16:34.627 --> 16:35.895
DELIVERY AT HAWAIIAN ELECTRIC

16:35.895 --> 16:37.296
COMPANY, OR HECO, AS THE UTILITY

16:37.296 --> 16:39.031
IS KNOWN.

16:39.031 --> 16:40.266
>> WHAT WAS HAPPENING WAS THAT

16:40.266 --> 16:42.635
POWER, WHICH NORMALLY FLOWS FROM

16:42.635 --> 16:44.937
THE GRID TO OUR CUSTOMERS, WERE

16:44.937 --> 16:47.240
NOW BEGINNING TO FLOW BACK INTO

16:47.240 --> 16:48.574
THOSE SUBSTATIONS.

16:48.574 --> 16:51.444
SUBSTATIONS WHICH WERE NOT 30,

16:51.444 --> 16:53.746
40 YEARS AGO DESIGNED TO OPERATE

16:53.746 --> 16:54.747
IN THAT MANNER.

16:54.747 --> 16:56.148
>> Reporter: IN ADDITION, HECO

16:56.148 --> 16:57.717
HAD A HARD TIME MEASURING ALL

16:57.717 --> 16:58.751
THAT SOLAR.

16:58.751 --> 17:00.052
>> RIGHT NOW, WE DON'T KNOW

17:00.052 --> 17:01.888
EXACTLY HOW MUCH POWER ROOFTOP

17:01.888 --> 17:03.155
SOLAR IS PRODUCING, AT ANY GIVEN

17:03.155 --> 17:04.290
MOMENT.

17:04.290 --> 17:05.358
>> Reporter: SO YOU CAN'T SEE AT

17:05.358 --> 17:07.660
ALL WHAT 10-12% OF YOUR CUSTOMER

17:07.660 --> 17:09.228
BASE IS PRODUCING?

17:09.228 --> 17:10.096
>> WE CANNOT.

17:10.096 --> 17:11.297
WE CANNOT SEE THAT.

17:11.297 --> 17:12.131
>> Reporter: BUT WHILE HECO

17:12.131 --> 17:13.499
STUDIED THE PROBLEM, HOMEOWNERS

17:13.499 --> 17:14.567
LIKE CARLTON HO WERE LEFT

17:14.567 --> 17:15.735
WAITING.

17:15.735 --> 17:16.836
IT HAD BEEN A YEAR-AND-A-HALF

17:16.836 --> 17:19.171
THAT HIS SYSTEM HAD SAT UNUSED.

17:19.171 --> 17:21.374
HO WAS LEFT PAYING HIS REGULAR

17:21.374 --> 17:22.541
ELECTRIC BILL: ABOUT $150 A

17:22.541 --> 17:23.576
MONTH.

17:23.576 --> 17:25.211
PLUS ANOTHER $240 A MONTH IN

17:25.211 --> 17:27.480
PAYMENTS FOR THE $23,000 SOLAR

17:27.480 --> 17:29.315
PANELS HE'D BOUGHT BUT COULDN'T

17:29.315 --> 17:30.950
USE.

17:30.950 --> 17:33.386
>> HAWAIIAN ELECTRIC NEEDS TO

17:33.386 --> 17:36.889
AND HAS TAKEN STEPS TO WORK WITH

17:36.889 --> 17:38.591
OUR CUSTOMERS TO FIND SOLUTIONS

17:38.591 --> 17:42.228
THAT WORKS FOR THEM AND WORKS

17:42.228 --> 17:43.462
FOR THE GRID.

17:43.462 --> 17:45.031
IT'S BEEN LEARNING MOMENTS, FOR

17:45.031 --> 17:47.233
US WITHIN THE UTILITY.

17:47.233 --> 17:48.334
>> Reporter: AND FOR THE SOLAR

17:48.334 --> 17:49.902
INDUSTRY WHICH TOOK A BIG HIT

17:49.902 --> 17:51.470
WHEN THE UTILITY SLOWED NEW

