CUSTOMERS, STILL THE MAJORITY,

18:12.525 --> 18:13.859
WERE PAYING MUCH MORE TO

18:13.859 --> 18:15.494
MAINTAIN THE PUBLIC GRID THAN

18:15.494 --> 18:17.029
THOSE WITH THEIR OWN PANELS ON

18:17.029 --> 18:19.365
THE ROOF, A DISPARITY HECO

18:19.365 --> 18:21.200
SUGGESTED COULD BE UNFAIR.

18:21.200 --> 18:22.401
>> IT MAKES SENSE THAT EVERYONE

18:22.401 --> 18:23.669
WHO USES THE GRID SHOULD PAY

18:23.669 --> 18:25.071
THEIR SHARE.

18:25.071 --> 18:26.238
>> Reporter: HECO SAYS THAT NON-

18:26.238 --> 18:27.740
SOLAR CUSTOMERS HAVE IN A SENSE

18:27.740 --> 18:29.275
BEEN SUBSIDIZING THOSE WITH

18:29.275 --> 18:31.110
ROOFTOP SOLAR WHEN IT COMES TO

18:31.110 --> 18:32.745
KEEPING THE GRID HUMMING.

18:32.745 --> 18:34.380
A COST SHIFT ESTIMATED AT MORE

